     
     
     Exam questions:


1. How do you print in C++?
A. cin>>”Hello World”;
B. Cout<<”Hello World”;
C. cin>>”Hello World”<<endl;
D. print(“Hello World”);


2. Which is not a loop structure?
A. For
B. Do while
C. While
D. Repeat Until


3. What punctuation ends most lines of C++ code?
A. . 
B. ; 
C. : 
D. ' 


4.  Which of the following shows the correct syntax for an if statement?
A. if expression
B. if { expression
C. if ( expression )
D. expression if


5. What punctuation is used to signal the beginning and end of code blocks?
A. { } 
B. -> and C. BEGIN and END 
D. ( and ) 


6. Which of the following is not a correct variable type?
A. float
B. real
C. int
D. double


7. Which of the following is the boolean operator for logical-and?
A. &
B. &&
C. |
D. |&


8.  Which of the following is a correct comment?
A. */ Comments */
B. ** Comment **
C. /* Comment */
D. { Comment }


9. Which of the following is not a correct variable type?
A. float
B. real
C. int
D. double


10. What is the correct value to return to the operating system upon the successful completion of a program?
A. -1 
B. 1 
C. 0 
D. Programs do not return a value.




The correct answers will be: 
1. b
2. d 
3. b
4. c
5. a 
6. b
7. b
8. c
9. b
10. c




Any suggestions/improvements are welcome! :)

